# Directive Reference

This page documents every directive and markdown enhancement currently supported by Marque.

@callout .info
  Standard markdown always works. Marque directives are additive: use them where structure and reusable patterns help.
@end callout

## Frontmatter

@row frontmatter-example
  @card .ghost
    Code:
    ```
    ---
    title: Team Handbook
    nav: handbook
    order: 2
    layout: sidebar
    theme: rustique
    width: 92
    description: Internal docs for contributors
    ---
    ```
  @end card

  @card .ghost
    Notes:

    - `title` sets the browser page title segment.
    - `nav` sets nav label and filename slug.
    - `order` controls nav ordering.
    - `layout` and `theme` override defaults for this page.
    - `width` overrides content width for this page.
  @end card
@end row frontmatter-example

## Row and card

@row row-card-example
  @card .ghost
    Code:
    ```
    @row pricing
      @card .accent starter
        ## Starter
        Great for tiny docs.
      @end card starter

      @card .dark pro
        ## Pro
        Advanced docs + demos.
      @end card pro
    @end row pricing
    ```
  @end card

  @card .ghost
    Result:

    @row pricing
      @card .accent starter
        ## Starter
        Great for tiny docs.
      @end card starter

      @card .dark pro
        ## Pro
        Advanced docs + demos.
      @end card pro
    @end row pricing
  @end card
@end row row-card-example

## Callout

@row callout-example
  @card .ghost
    Code:
    ```
    @callout .warn
      Watch for breaking changes when renaming nav slugs.
    @end callout
    ```
  @end card

  @card .ghost
    Result:

    @callout .warn
      Watch for breaking changes when renaming nav slugs.
    @end callout
  @end card
@end row callout-example

Variants: `.info`, `.warn`, `.danger`, `.ok`.

