## Markdown enhancements

@row markdown-enhancements
  @card .ghost
    Code:
    ```
    [Read docs ?](/directives.html)
    [Download release](/downloads/marque.zip){.download}

    :badge[Stable]{.ok}
    :badge[Preview]{.warn}
    ```
  @end card

  @card .ghost
    Result:

    [Read docs ?](/directives.html)
    [Download release](#){.download}

    :badge[Stable]{.ok}
    :badge[Preview]{.warn}
  @end card
@end row markdown-enhancements

The download-link color trick:

1. Use a custom class in markdown link shorthand: `{.download}`.
2. Style that class in your theme: `.mq-btn.download { ... }`.

## Generic directives

Unknown directives become generic wrappers, so this:

```
@feature-grid
  ...
@end feature-grid
```

renders as `.mq-feature-grid`, which you can target in theme CSS.

## Practical tips

- Use directive names (`@row pricing`) for readability.
- Keep pages markdown-first, then add directive structure.
- Prefer reusable patterns over one-off custom HTML.
